Nine court cases that seek to quash the nomination and appointment of Nairobi Deputy Governor Anne Kananu Mwenda will be heard and determined by a three-judge bench due to the novel questions of law raised by the petitioners. 

According to a notice issued by the High Court Deputy Registrar, Acting Chief Justice Philomena Mwilu has appointed Justice Juma Said Chitembwe the presiding judge of the bench while members are Justices Weldon Korir and Wilfrida Okwany. 



