However, he explained that in allowing the vetting process to continue, the court acted in the best interest of  Nairobi County and of the country at large and in the public interest. He said the court had no option but to avoid a looming constitutional crisis. 

This is because when the court suspended a decision of the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission (IEBC) to call a by-election, it meant that IEBC would not proceed with any of the preparations towards the holding of the by-election. 

The petitions will be mentioned before the bench on February 25. With a year to 2022 polls and Jubilee having no strong contender for city seat in mini-poll, a twin plan was hatched for someone to succeed Sonko. A litany of court cases put paid to the by-election by the IEBC that was to be held today. The lender of last resort has now given the government a total of Sh14.8 billion since last year. A total of 114 ward representatives vote in favour of the draft. A litany of court cases put paid to the by-election by the IEBC that was to be held today.